              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                These Terms apply to all clients who bring their pets to Lillian Ruff Pet Spa for grooming services. Please read these Terms carefully before scheduling or bringing your pet for a grooming appointment. By using our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree to these Terms, you may not use our grooming services.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                We reserve the right to update, change, or replace any part of these Terms by posting updates on our website at lillianruffpetspa.com. It is your responsibility to check this page periodically for changes. Your continued use of our services following the posting of any changes constitutes acceptance of those changes.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 1 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-green/10 to-emerald-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-brand-green font-bold text-sm">1</span>
                General Conditions
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                We reserve the right to refuse service to any client or pet for any reason at any time, including but not limited to the pet's health, behavior, or the client's failure to comply with these Terms.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                You agree not to hold Lillian Ruff Pet Spa responsible for any pre-existing conditions, whether known or unknown, that may affect your pet during or after the grooming process, except as expressly stated in these Terms.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                The headings used in this agreement are included for convenience only and will not limit or otherwise affect these Terms.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 2 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-green/10 to-emerald-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-brand-green font-bold text-sm">2</span>
                Health or Medical Problems & Senior Pets
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Grooming procedures can sometimes be stressful, particularly for senior pets or pets with health problems. Such stress can expose hidden medical issues or aggravate existing conditions during or after the grooming session. In the best interest of your pet, by agreeing to these Terms, you grant Lillian Ruff Pet Spa permission to obtain immediate veterinary treatment for your pet if we deem it necessary during the grooming process. We will make every effort to contact you first and take your pet to your authorized veterinarian, or to the nearest available veterinarian if yours is unavailable. You agree that all expenses for veterinary care will be your responsibility and will be covered by you, the pet owner.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 3 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-green/10 to-emerald-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-brand-green font-bold text-sm">3</span>
                Mat Removal
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Pets with matted coats require extra attention during grooming. Mats that are left in a pet's coat can tighten over time, potentially strangling the pet's skin or causing it to tear open. At Lillian Ruff Pet Spa, we prioritize your pet's comfort and will not continuously demat a pet if it causes serious or undue stress. Mats can be very difficult to remove and may require shaving the pet. Removing a heavily matted coat carries risks, including nicks, cuts, or abrasions due to warts, moles, or skin folds trapped in the mats. Heavy matting can also trap moisture and urine near the pet's skin, leading to mold, fungus, or bacterial growth, which may cause skin irritations that predate the grooming process. In severe cases, torn skin from mats can harbor maggots.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                After-effects of mat removal may include itchiness, hematomas, skin redness, self-inflicted irritations or abrasions, and failure of the hair to regrow. Shaved pets are also prone to sunburn and should have sunscreen applied daily or be kept out of the sun until the hair grows sufficiently to protect the skin. In some cases, pets may exhibit brief behavioral changes following mat removal.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Prevention is the best defense against matting. We strongly recommend scheduling regular grooming appointments to maintain your pet's coat. Lillian Ruff Pet Spa will not be held responsible for any injuries or after-effects resulting from mat removal, including those listed above.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 4 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-green/10 to-emerald-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-brand-green font-bold text-sm">4</span>
                Accidents
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                While we use extreme caution and care in all grooming situations, there is always a possibility that an accident may occur. Grooming equipment is sharp, and possible issues such as cuts, nicks, scratches, or quicking of nails may happen, especially with an excited or uncooperative pet. We make every effort to ensure your pet is groomed as safely as possible, but an excited pet can be dangerous to work with. By agreeing to these Terms, you acknowledge these risks and agree that Lillian Ruff Pet Spa will not be held liable for such accidents, provided we have exercised reasonable care.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 5 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-green/10 to-emerald-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-brand-green font-bold text-sm">5</span>
                Parasites
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                If you suspect your pet has fleas or ticks, you must take prompt and thorough action to address the issue. Flea infestations can lead to tapeworms and other health problems for your pet. If fleas or ticks are discovered during the grooming process, your pet will be treated with a natural product to kill the parasites, and you will be charged for the use of flea shampoo. Please note that Lillian Ruff Pet Spa does not use pesticide dips or sprays on pets. Ticks will be removed for an additional charge. If ticks are found, we strongly recommend having your pet tested for Lyme Disease, as parasites pose a health hazard to both your pet and humans. You agree to cover any additional charges for parasite treatment as outlined.
              </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 6 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
